==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lithotint
<hw>Lith"o*tint</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Litho-</ets>
+ <ets>tint</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A kind of lithography by
which the effect of a tinted drawing is produced, as if made with India
ink.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A picture produced by this process.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lithotome</ent>⟦br⟧
